ward%20to%20a%20big%20tax%20return%20in%20the%20next%20few%20weeks.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EReceiving%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20back%20from%20the%20IRS%20isn't%20necessarily%20a%20good%20thing%2C%20though.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHere's%20how%20you%20can%20optimize%20your%20tax%20return%20for%20the%20biggest%20savings.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20thing%20that%20makes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworking-multiple-jobs-high-tax-burden-lower-tips-donations-scorp-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efiling%20your%20taxes%3C%2Fa%3E%20less%20of%20a%20chore%20is%20the%20knowledge%20that%20you%20could%20be%20getting%20a%20few%20thousand%20dollars%20back%20when%20your%20tax%20return%20hits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20a%20big%20tax%20return%20isn't%20necessarily%20a%20good%20thing%2C%20according%20to%20Ashley%20Weeks%2C%20a%20wealth%20advisor%20at%20TD%20Wealth.%20In%20fact%2C%20you%20might%20want%20to%20take%20steps%20to%20minimize%20your%20tax%20return%20in%20coming%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20tax%20refund%20is%20a%20reimbursement%20made%20to%20the%20taxpayer%20for%20the%20excess%20state%20and%20federal%20taxes%20they've%20paid%20throughout%20the%20year.%20So%20when%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Firs-employees-tax-season-risks-rto-challenges-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIRS%3C%2Fa%3E%20pays%20you%20money%20after%20you%20file%2C%20it%20means%20that%20you've%20overpaid%20the%20government%20during%20the%20tax%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20essentially%20an%20interest-free%20loan%20made%20to%20the%20government%20that%20you%20only%20get%20back%20in%20April%20of%20the%20year%20after%20you%20issued%20the%20loan%2C%26quot%3B%20Weeks%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20first%20thing%20I%20tell%20clients%20when%20they%20get%20a%20larger-than-expected%20refund%20is%20to%20take%20a%20breath%2C%20figure%20out%20why%20the%20refund%20was%20so%20big%2C%20and%20make%20some%20adjustments%20for%20the%20next%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20Weeks%20added.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20getting%20more%20than%20%241%2C000%20back%2C%20there's%20probably%20room%20for%20optimizing%20your%20withholding%20strategy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20reason%20why%20clients%20get%20a%20big%20tax%20refund%20is%20because%20they're%20overpaying%20taxes%20from%20their%20W-2%20job%20during%20the%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20that's%20the%20case%2C%20Weeks%20recommends%20checking%20in%20with%20your%20HR%20department%20and%20adjusting%20your%20Form%20W-4.%20Form%20W-4%20determines%20how%20much%20tax%20your%20employer%20withholds%2C%20and%20the%20IRS%20recommends%20filling%20out%20a%20new%20one%20each%20year%2C%20or%20whenever%20your%20financial%20situation%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20good%20idea%20regularly%20check%20on%20your%20W-4%20as%20time%20goes%20on%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20information%20is%20accurate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20form%20that%20very%20often%20people%20only%20fill%20out%20when%20they%20start%20with%20their%20employer%20and%20don't%20revisit%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Weeks%20said.%20%26quot%3BObviously%2C%20life%20changes.%20Income%20can%20go%20up%2C%20there%20can%20be%20outside%20sources%20of%20income%20from%20side%20hustles%2C%20people%20have%20kids%2C%20people%20have%20more%20deductions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReal%20estate%20investors%20and%20self-employed%20individuals%20may%20also%20experience%20over-withholding%20issues%2C%20Weeks%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIncome%20taxes%20are%20collected%20on%20a%20continuous%20basis%2C%20which%20is%20why%20your%20employer%20takes%20money%20from%20each%20paycheck.%20For%20those%20earning%20income%20independently%2C%20the%20IRS%20requires%20you%20to%20pay%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffile-taxes-extension-october-deadline-paperwork-retirement-plans-small-business-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eestimated%20taxes%3C%2Fa%3E%20quarterly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20calculate%20estimates%20from%20what%20you%20paid%20in%20the%20previous%20year%2C%20or%20you%20can%20annualize%20based%20on%20how%20much%20you've%20earned%20so%20far%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverestimating%20your%20quarterly%20taxes%20will%20result%20in%20a%20bigger%20tax%20return.%20If%20you%20think%20you're%20overpaying%20your%20quarterly%20taxes%2C%20you%20can%20adjust%20the%20number%20on%20Form%201040-ES.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlenty%20of%20taxpayers%20like%20the%20feeling%20of%20getting%20a%20lump%20sum%20in%20April.%20Some%20of%20Weeks'%20clients%20think%20of%20a%20tax%20return%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bforced%20savings%20mechanism.%26quot%3B%20For%20those%20who%20get%20one%2C%20Weeks%20recommends%20using%20the%20tax%20return%20to%20pay%20off%20high-interest%20debt%20and%20build%20up%20an%20emergency%20fund.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20tax%20return%20comes%20at%20a%20cost.%20If%20you%20hadn't%20overpaid%20your%20taxes%20during%20the%20year%2C%20you%20could%20have%20been%20using%20the%20extra%20money%20to%20pay%20off%20debt%2C%20save%20up%20for%20a%20big%20purchase%2C%20or%20invest.%20Ideally%2C%20you%20want%20to%20keep%20more%20of%20your%20money%20easily%20accessible%20year-round.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20probably%20not%20the%20optimal%20strategy%20because%2C%20again%2C%20the%20government%20holds%20that%20money%20and%20doesn't%20pay%20any%20interest%2C%26quot%3B%20Weeks%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20can%20be%20damaging%20if%2C%20during%20the%20tax%20year%2C%20someone%20has%20to%20go%20into%20additional%20credit%20card%20debt%20to%20pay%20expenses%2C%20or%20they%20reduce%20their%20retirement%20savings%20rate%20simply%20because%20they%20don't%20have%20the%20liquidity%20on%20hand%20that%20they%20should%20have%20because%20the%20money%20is%20being%20held%20by%20the%20government.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftax-refund-2025-irs-filing-deadline-personal