and%20green%20card%20hopefuls%2C%20as%20it%20shows%20a%20significant%20retrogression%20in%20the%20employment-based%20fifth%20preference%20(EB-5)%20category%20for%20Indians.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPer%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22No%20Follow%2C%20No%20Index%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftravel.state.gov%2Fcontent%2Ftravel%2Fen%2Flegal%2Fvisa-law0%2Fvisa-bulletin%2F2025%2Fvisa-bulletin-for-may-2025.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edocument%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20EB-5%20Unreserved%20category%20visa%20for%20Indians%20would%20move%20backward%20by%20over%20six%20months%20to%20May%201%2C%202019.%20China%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20remains%20on%20January%2022%2C%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHigh%20demand%20and%20number%20use%20by%20India%20in%20the%20EB-5%20unreserved%20visa%20categories%2C%20combined%20with%20increased%20Rest%20of%20World%20demand%20and%20number%20use%2C%20made%20it%20necessary%20to%20further%20retrogress%20the%20India%20final%20action%20date%20to%20hold%20number%20use%20within%20the%20maximum%20allowed%20under%20the%20FY-2025%20annual%20limits%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bulletin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20May%20Visa%20Bulletin%20Say%20About%20Other%20Categories%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEmployment-Based%2C%20First%20Preference%20(EB-1)%20Category%3A%20There%20is%20no%20change%20for%20the%20EB-1%20category%20as%20the%20cutoff%20date%20for%20India%20remains%20at%20February%202%2C%202022%2C%20while%20for%20China%2C%20it%20remains%20November%208%2C%202022.%20%C2%A0All%20other%20countries%20will%20continue%20to%20be%20current%20in%20the%20EB1%20category.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEmployment-Based%2C%20Second%20Preference%20(EB-2)%20Category%3A%20The%20EB-2%20category%20will%20also%20remain%20unchanged%20for%20Indians%20and%20Chinese%20nationals.%20For%20India%2C%20the%20cutoff%20date%20remains%20January%201%2C%202013%2C%20while%20for%20China%20it%20remains%20October%201%2C%202020.%20The%20EB2%20cutoff%20dat