use%20we%20thought%20homesteading%20would%20save%20us%20money.%20It%20didn't.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223145%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Three%20goats%20looking%20through%20a%20hole%20in%20a%20fence%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67f94bf9a466d2b74ab2f560%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222359%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20still%20keeps%20goats%20on%20her%20farm%2C%20even%20though%20she's%20no%20longer%20a%20homesteader.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Kirsten%20Lie-Nielsen%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAbout%2010%20years%20ago%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20decided%20to%20try%20homesteading.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWe%20wanted%20to%20be%20self-sufficient%20and%20moved%20to%20a%2093-acre%20farm%20in%20rural%20Maine.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOver%20time%2C%20we%20realized%20that%20it%20was%20harder%20than%20we%20thought%20and%20didn't%20actually%20save%20us%20money.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202015%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpacking-tips-cross-country-move-what-to-pack-regrets-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Epacked%20up%20our%20belongings%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%94%20including%20half%20a%20dozen%20geese%20and%20a%20library%20of%20self-sufficiency%20how-tos%20%E2%80%94%20and%20moved%20our%20lives%20from%20two%20acres%20in%20a%20coastal%20suburb%20to%20a%2093-acre%20farm%20in%20rural%20Maine.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20dream%20was%20to%20create%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-millennials-people-are-homesteading-control-uncontrollable-food-feel-safe-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eself-reliant%20life%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Having%20grown%20up%20on%20stories%20of%20rural%20heroes%20from%20Thoreau%20to%20the%20Nearings%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20embody%20an%20alternative%20to%20the%20life%20paths%20I%20observed%20around%20me.%20I%20did%20not%20want%20to%20climb%20any%20corporate%20ladders%20or%20buy%20into%20consumer%20culture.%20Instead%2C%20I%20believed%20I%20could%20scratch%20a%20more%20unconventional%20lifestyle%20out%20of%20Maine's%20rocky%20soil.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223987%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Geese%20walking%20on%20a%20field%20toward%20the%20camera.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67f94b5ca466d2b74ab2f52b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222990%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAfter%20moving%20to%20a%2093-acre%20farm%2C%20the%20author%20learned%20that%20self-sufficiency%20is%20more%20difficult%20than%20she%20thought.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Kirsten%20Lie-Nielsen%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227e7dd475-f455-4de8-8665-77f01742f66a%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20started%20with%20chickens%20but%20realized%20that%20wouldn't%20actually%20lower%20the%20price%20of%20eggs%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELike%20many%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-homesteading-is-growing-trend-with-millenials-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ebeginning%20homesteaders%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20I%20was%20blissfully%20unaware%20of%20the%20cost%20of%20the%20lifestyle.%20In%20my%20mind%2C%20and%20according%20to%20all%20the%20books%20I%20read%2C%20we%20could%20reduce%20our%20income%20needs%20by%20limiting%20our%20expenses%20and%20cutting%20out%20'wasteful'%20spending%2C%20like%20nights%20out%20and%20new%20clothes.%20Our%20needs%20would%20be%20further%20reduced%20by%20cutting%20out%20trips%20to%20the%20grocery%20store%2C%20instead%20growing%20our%20own%20food.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20knew%20that%20we%20would%20not%20be%20immediately%20self-sufficient.%20In%20fact%2C%20until%20the%20pandemic%20made%20working%20from%20home%20a%20necessity%2C%20I%20commuted%20in%20to%20work%20on%20rural%20country%20roads%20throughout%20our%20life%20on%20the%20homestead.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20started%20with%20chickens%2C%20like%20many%20other%20homesteaders%20do.%20Chickens%20have%20always%20been%20the%20'gateway%20livestock'%20because%20they%20are%20small%20and%20easy%20to%20house%2C%20it's%20not%20hard%20to%20find%20someone%20to%20take%20care%20of%20chickens%20if%20you%20leave%20for%20the%20weekend%2C%20and%20chicks%20are%20relatively%20inexpensive%20at%20your%20local%20Tractor%20Supply.%20These%20days%2C%20chickens%20are%20more%20popular%20than%20they%20have%20ever%20been.%20With%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fegg-prices-expensive-avian-bird-flu-changing-tastes-cage-free-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eprice%20of%20eggs%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20soaring%2C%20people%20believe%20that%20they%20can%20get%20'free%20eggs'%20by%20putting%20some%20chickens%20in%20their%20backyard.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20problem%20is%20that%20chickens%20are%20actually%20a%20terrible%20way%20to%20get%20cheaper%20eggs.%20Over%20our%20years%20of%20homesteading%2C%20we%20learned%20that%20the%20costs%20to%20house%2C%20feed%2C%20and%20care%20for%20a%20few%20backyard%20chickens%20far%20outweigh%20the%20cost%20of%20simply%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-egg-supplies-normalizing-prices-to-follow-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Epaying%20for%20eggs%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20even%20at%20current%20record-breaking%20high%20prices.%20When%20we%20looked%20at%20our%20budget%2C%20we%20realized%20we%20were%20always%20paying%20more%20for%20chicken%20feed%20than%20we%20were%20saving%20on%20eggs.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENot%20only%20that%2C%20we%20quickly%20learned%20that%20chickens%20prefer%20to%20lay%20in%20spring%20and%20summer%20and%20sometimes%20don't%20provide%20eggs%20all%20winter%2C%20and%20they%20seemed%20to%20be%20a%20magnet%20for%20predators%20that%20would%20find%20any%20crack%20in%20the%20coop%20and%20decimate%20our%20flock.%20Birds%20can%20also%20be%20a%20health%20risk%20%E2%80%94%20we%20eventually%20lost%20our%20flock%20to%20Avian%20Flu%20in%20the%20spring%20of%202022%2C%20a%20disease%20that%20has%20grown%20more%20threatening%20to%20humans%20over%20the%20years.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20majority%20of%20our%20livestock%20choices%20ran%20us%20into%20similar%20problems.%20In%20order%20to%20get%20milk%20from%20goats%2C%20you%20have%20to%20breed%20them.%20That%20meant%20that%20every%20year%2C%20our%20Nigerian%20Dwarf%20goat%20would%20give%20birth%20to%20between%20one%20and%20five%20kids%2C%20and%20because%20we%20did%20not%20want%20an%20ever-expanding%20herd%2C%20we%20needed%20to%20sell%20them.%20The%20problem%20was%2C%20this%20was%20always%20a%20struggle%3B%20this%20adorable%20goat%20breed%20had%20become%20very%20popular%2C%20and%20every%20homesteader%20nearby%20had%20goat%20kids%20for%20sale.%20Visits%20from%20the%20vet%20were%20necessary%20to%20keep%20our%20herd%20healthy%2C%20and%20fencing%20was%20an%20ongoing%20cost%20%E2%80%94%20the%20saying%20among%20farmers%20is%20that%20a%20fence%20that%20can%20hold%20water%20can%20hold%20a%20goat.%20Because%20of%20their%20escape%20antics%2C%20goats%20also%20proved%20ineffectual%20at%20clearing%20brush%2C%20the%20fringe%20benefit%20we%20hoped%20they'd%20offer.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20pigs%20walking%20on%20a%20grassy%20field.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67f94b9fa466d2b74ab2f544%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20realized%20that%20being%20a%20homesteader%20would%20not%20save%20her%20as%20much%20money%20as%20she%20thought.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Kirsten%20Lie-Nielsen%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22940be3b6-f226-4c36-92eb-f210971d0e4b%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIt's%20harder%20to%20be%20self-sufficient%20than%20I%20thought%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20perspective%20on%20homesteading%20at%20the%20beginning%20may%20have%20been%20naive%2C%20but%20it%20was%20reinforced%20by%20countless%20homesteading%20writers%20and%20influencers%20who%20promote%20the%20lifestyle%20as%20sustainable.%20It%20took%20years%20for%20me%20to%20accept%20the%20realities%20of%20farm%20life.%20In%20the%20summer%20months%2C%20it%20was%20easy%20to%20replace%20many%20groceries%20with%20homegrown%20produce%2C%20but%20in%20winter%2C%20stored%20root%20vegetables%20and%20pickles%20became%20tiresome.%20While%20our%20animals%20did%20help%20us%20manage%20our%20land%2C%20they%20never%20did%20the%20work%20the%20way%20equipment%20could%20or%20saved%20us%20backbreaking%20labor.%20Few%2C%20if%20any%2C%20homesteads%20are%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foff-grid-lifestyle-is-not-for-everyone-and-thats-ok-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Etruly%20self-sufficient%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20And%20those%20that%20are%20often%20only%20manage%20such%20a%20lifestyle%20through%20a%20radical%20lifestyle.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20Thoreau%20%E2%80%94%20seen%20by%20many%20as%20the%20father%20of%20the%20self-reliance%20movement%20thanks%20to%20his%20seminal%20work%20Walden%20%E2%80%94%20had%20his%20mother%20do%20his%20laundry%20for%20him%20while%20he%20was%20living%20'self-sufficiently'%20at%20Walden%20Pond.%20The%20Nearings%20relied%20on%20a%20steady%20stream%20of%20eager%20apprentices%20and%20income%20from%20books%20and%20speaking%20tours.%20A%20self-sufficient%20life%20did%20not%20mean%20frolicking%20with%20baby%20goats%20in%20the%20green%20fields.%20Instead%2C%20we%20learned%20the%20hard%20way%20that%20it%20looked%20more%20like%20spending%20early%20mornings%20injecti