0man%20who%20is%20supposed%20to%20be%20a%20US%20importer.%20In%20the%20video%2C%20the%20man%20addresses%20the%20American%20public%2C%20especially%20Trump%20supporters%2C%20warning%20that%20ordinary%20citizens%20-not%20foreign%20countries-%20will%20have%20to%20bear%20the%20cost%20of%20Trump's%20aggressive%20trade%20policies%2C%20which%20would%20hike%20the%20prices%20of%20imported%20items%20and%20burden%20consumers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EForeign%20countries%20pay%20the%20tariffs%3F%20No%E2%80%94US%20businesses%20pay%2C%20then%20pass%20costs%20to%20you.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnTariffs%20don't%20bring%20manufacturing%20back.%20They're%20just%20a%20tax%20on%20Americans.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FiOw3IrFpiQ%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FiOw3IrFpiQ%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20Mao%20Ning%20%E6%AF%9B%E5%AE%81%20(%40SpoxCHN_MaoNing)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FSpoxCHN_MaoNing%2Fstatus%2F1911206346965602406%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EApril%2012%2C%202025%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BForeign%20countries%20pay%20the%20tariffs%3F%20No%20-%20US%20businesses%20pay%2C%20then%20pass%20costs%20to%20you.%20Tariffs%20don't%20bring%20manufacturing%20back.%20They're%20just%20a%20tax%20on%20Americans%2C%26quot%3B%20Mao%20captioned%20the%20post.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EUS-China%20Trade%20War%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20post%20comes%20amid%20escalating%20economic%20tension%20between%20the%20world's%20two%20largest%20economies%20after%20US%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20imposed%20hefty%20taxes%20on%20Chinese%20goods%2C%20calling%20them%20%26quot%3Breciprocal%20tariffs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20on%20Wednesday%20increased%20the%20stakes%20in%20a%20trade%20war%20that%20threatens%20to%20upend%20global%20supply%20chains%20by%20raising%20tariffs%20on%20Chinese%20goods%20to%20145%20per%20cent.%20In%20retaliation%2C%20Beijing%20increased%20its%20tariffs%20on%20US%20imports%20to%20125%20per%20cent%20on%20Friday.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20tit-for-tat%20tariff%20increases%20by%20the%20US%20and%20China%20stand%20to%20make%20goods%20trade%20between%20the%20world's%20two%20largest%20economies%20impossible%2C%20analysts%20say.%20That%20commerce%20was%20worth%20more%20than%20%24650%20billion%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20pretty%20much%20can%20do%20what%20we%20want%20to%20do%2C%20but%20we%20want%20to%20be%20fair.%20We%20can%20set%20the%20tariff%2C%20and%20they%20can%20choose%20not%20to%20deal%20with%20us%20or%20they%20can%20choose%20to%20pay%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20said%20on%20Air%20Force%20One%2C%20repeating%20his%20contention%20that%20US-imposed%20tariffs%20are%20paid%20by%20foreign%20exporters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20Tariffs%20Work%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20such%20levies%20can%20inflict%20pain%20on%20the%20exporter%20by%20making%20its%20products%20less%20competitive%2C%20tariffs%20are%20paid%20by%20the%20importer%2C%20which%20often%20passes%20the%20additional%20cost%20on%20to%20the%20consumer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrump%20Says%20Negotiations%20On%20Table%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%2C%20who%20said%20on%20Friday%20he%20was%20comfortable%20with%20the%20tariffs%20on%20China%2C%20has%20suggested%20that%20a%20deal%20with%20Beijing%20could%20be%20in%20the%20offing%2C%20too%2C%20heaping%20praise%20on%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20despite%20their%20differences%20over%20trade.%20But%20there%20were%20no%20signs%20that%20the%20world's%20two%20largest%20economies%20were%20ready%20to%20back%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20president%20made%20it%20very%20clear%3A%20When%20the%20United%20States%20is%20punched%2C%20he%20will%20punch%20back%20harder%2C%26quot%3B%20White%20House%20Press%20Secretary%20Karoline%20Leavitt%20told%20reporters%20on%20Friday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrump's%20Exemptions%20From%20China%20Tariffs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Trump%20administration%20granted%20exclusions%20from%20steep%20reciprocal%20tariffs%20to%20smartphones%2C%20computers%20and%20some%20other%20electronics%20imported%20largely%20from%20China%2C%20providing%20a%20big%20break%20to%20tech%20firms%20like%20Apple%20that%20rely%20on%20imported%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20notice%20to%20shippers%2C%20the%20US%20Customs%20and%20Border%20Protection%20agency%20published%20a%20list%20of%20tariff%20codes%20excluded%20from%20the%20import%20taxes%2C%20with%20retroactive%20effect%20from%204%3A01%20am%20(GMT)%20on%20April%205.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20featured%2020%20product%20categories%2C%20including%20the%20broad%208471%20code%20for%20all%20computers%2C%20laptops%2C%20disc%20drives%20and%20automatic%20data%20processing.%20It%20also%20included%20semiconductor%20devices%2C%20equipment%2C%20memory%20chips%20and%20flat%20panel%20displays.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20notice%20gave%20no%20explanation%20for%20the%20move%2C%20but%20the%20late-night%20exclusion%20provides%20welcome%20relief%20to%20major%20technology%20firms%20such%20as%20Apple%2C%20Dell%20Technologies%20and%20many%20other%20importers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump's%20action%20also%20excludes%20the%20specified%20electronics%20from%20his%2010%20per%20cent%20%26quot%3Bbaseline%26quot%3B%20tariffs%20on%20goods%20from%20most%20countries%20other%20than%20China%2C%20easing%20import%20costs%20for%20semiconductors%20from%20Taiwan%20and%20Apple%20iPhones%20produced%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1744536060000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-04%2Fc1lbl7f4_donald-trump-xi-jinping-us-china-tariff-war_625x300_09_April_25.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fchinas-message-to-us-citizens-amid-donald-trumps-tariff-war-tax-on-americans-8154104%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Amid%20the%20escalating%20trade%20war%20between%20the%20United%20States%20and%20China%2C%20Beijing%20seems%20to%20have%20altered%20its%20strategy%20of%20dealing%20with%20Washington%20by%20aiming%20its%20message%20directly%20at%20the%20American%20public%20instead%20of%20the%20Trump%20administration.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20Insects%2C%20Smallest%20Animals%20Survive%20Antarctica%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIn%20Antarctica's%20freezing%20depths%2C%20tiny%20creatures%20have%20mastered%20survival%20tactics%20that%20could%20unlock%20secrets%20to%20extreme%20cold%20resistance%2C%20with%20implications%20for%20science%20and%20medicine.%20Some%20of%20the%20most%20intense%20battles%20against%20the%20environment%20are%20waged%20by%20the%20smallest%20of%20creatures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20it's%20cold%2C%20we%2C%20as%20warm-blooded%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbyjus.com%2Fbiology%2Fwhat-is-an-endothermic-animal%2F%23%3A%257E%3Atext%3DAn%2520endotherm%252C%2520as%2520the%2520name%2Cmammals%2520of%2520the%2520animal%2520kingdom.%5C%22%3Eendothermic%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%20animals%20simply%20put%20on%20a%20coat.%20Other%20endotherms%2C%20can%20be%20large%2C%20fat%20or%20furry%20to%20insulate%20their%20body%20from%20the%20cold.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGenerating%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Farticles%2FPMC6938711%2F%5C%22%3Eyour%20own%20body%20heat%2C%20however%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0requires%20a%20lot%20of%20energy.%20Insects%20do%20not%20do%20not%20do%20this.%20The%20heat%20they%20need%20for%20metabolism%20and%20growth%20comes%20from%20the%20environment.%20This%20is%20partly%20how%20they%20are%20so%20abundant%20around%20the%20world.%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.biologists.com%2Fjeb%2Farticle%2F226%2F21%2Fjeb245782%2F334546%2FSeasonal-energetics-are-insects-constrained-by%5C%22%3EThey%20need%20less%20energy%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20grow%20compared%20with%20warm-blooded%20animals%20like%20mammals%20and%20are%20great%20at%20exploiting%20this%20advantage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20being%20able%20to%20generate%20your%20own%20body%20heat%20is%20a%20problem%20for%20insects%20in%20cold%20places.%20They%20are%20at%20the%20mercy%20of%20the%20environmental%20temperature%20and%20can%20only%20grow%2C%20develop%20and%20feed%20when%20it%20is%20warm%20enough.%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbesjournals.onlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2F10.1111%2Fj.1365-2435.2008.01489.x%5C%22%3ETypically%20this%20optimum%20temperature%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20around%2020%C2%B0C.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%20some%20insects%20survive%20when%20temperatures%20drop%20below%20freezing.%20Generally%2C%20when%20the%20temperature%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mayoclinic.org%2Fdiseases-conditions%2Ffrostbite%2Fsymptoms-causes%2Fsyc-20372656.%5C%22%3Egoes%20below%200%C2%B0C%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0this%20causes%20damage%20to%20animal%20cells%20and%20even%20death.%20This%20cell%20damage%20is%20what%20causes%20frostbite.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20insects%20use%20one%20of%20two%20simple%20strategies.%20Freeze%20tolerance%20or%20freeze%20avoidance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20they%20produce%20cryoprotectants%2C%20such%20as%20glycerol%2C%20which%20lower%20their%20freezing%20point.%20This%20allows%20the%20animal%20to%20undergo%20supercooling%20without%20freezing.%20Some%20generate%20antifreeze%20proteins%20that%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.missoulabutterflyhouse.org%2Finsect-winter-ecology-freeze-avoidance%2F%5C%22%3Estop%20ice%20crystals%20from%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0forming%20in%20their%20tissue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMites%20are%20common%20in%20the%20Antarctic%20%E2%80%93%20there%20are%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1080%2F00222939300770171%3Fcasa_token%3DbyO9-Z2fzTAAAAAA%3ACo7DUf2hMOucSc9FR4ms75rK-1zL46HsrFXeBghT1Y9dALuPOfO3FNDgFzrbHgtEkzCd0e_3o2su%5C%22%3Ehundreds%20of%20species%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Some%20even%20live%20in%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fagupubs.onlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2F10.1029%2FAR010p0041%23%3A%257E%3Atext%3DTwo%2520species%2520of%2520nasal%2520mites%2520and%25202%2CHyland%2520(family%2520Rhinonyssidae)%2520parasitizes%2520the%2520Ad%25C3%25A9lie%2520penguin.%5C%22%3Enasal%20cavities%20of%20penguins%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Penguin%20noses%20provide%20not%20only%20a%20source%20of%20food%20for%20the%20mites%20that%20feed%20on%20the%20penguins'%20dead%20skin%20cells%2C%20but%20also%20a%20warm%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20some%20Antarctic%20mites%2C%20which%20don't%20rely%20on%20a%20host%2C%20such%20as%C2%A0%3Cem%3EHalozetes%20belgicae%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20are%20freeze-avoiding%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.biologists.com%2Fjeb%2Farticle%2F210%2F4%2F593%2F17228%2FPlasticity-and-superplasticity-in-the-acclimation%5C%22%3Eusing%20antifreeze%20compounds%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20lower%20the%20freezing%20point%20of%20their%20body%20to%20well%20below%200%C2%B0C.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20smallest%20land%20animals%20in%20Antarctica%20are%20the%20springtails%2C%20related%20to%20primitive%20insects%20but%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmdc.mo.gov%2Fdiscover-nature%2Ffield-guide%2Fspringtails%5C%22%3Elacking%20some%20of%20the%20features%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0we%20see%20in%20modern%20insects.%20For%20example%2C%20their%20mouthparts%20are%20internal%20whereas%20insects%20have%20external%20mouthparts.%20One%20springtail%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3EGomphiocephalus%20hodgsoni%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20can%20reach%20a%20temperature%20of%20-38%C2%B0C%20before%20it%20freezes.%20It%20is%20a%20small%20species%20of%20only%201-2%20millimetres%20in%20length%20but%20important%20for%20the%20Antarctic%20soil%20ecosystem%2C%20fulfilling%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cambridge.org%2Fcore%2Fjournals%2Fantarctic-science%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fcold-tolerance-of-the-antarctic-springtail-gomphiocephalus-hodgsoni-collembola-hypogastruridae%2FE47F3D2E4C4AC555795759E9C4403879%5C%22%3Ean%20important%20function%20as%20a%20decomposer%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20organic%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.inaturalist.org%2Ftaxa%2F353460-Belgica-antarctica%5C%22%3EThe%20midge%20species%20%3Cem%3EBelgica%20Antarctica%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20however%2C%20is%20the%20only%20true%20insect%20found%20in%20Antarctica.%20It%20endures%20many%20periods%20of%20sub-zero%20temperatures%20throughout%20its%20life%20and%20has%20some%20unique%20strategies%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20hostile%20Antarctic%20climate.%20This%20species%20takes%20two%20years%20to%20reach%20adulthood%20%E2%80%93%20which%20in%20insect%20time%20is%20quite%20the%20long%20while.%20Some%20insects%20such%20as%20aphids%20have%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmyntuac-my.sharepoint.com%2Fpersonal%2Falex_dittrich_ntu_ac_uk%2FDocuments%2FConversation%2520articles%2FArctic%2520midges%2F(https%3A%2Fwww.rhs.org.uk%2Fbiodiversity%2Faphids).%5C%22%3Emultiple%20generations%20in%20a%20year%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBelgica%20Antarctica%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Farticles%2Fs41598-025-86617-4%5C%22%3Ecan%20tolerate%20ice%20crystals%20forming%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20its%20body%20by%20minimising%20the%20damage%20they%20do%20to%20tissue.%20It%20can%20also%20lose%20water%20from%20its%20body%20through%20a%20semi-permeable%20outer%20membrane%2C%20removing%20molecules%20that%20could%20form%20into%20ice%20crystals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20among%20the%20most%20dominant%20animals%20in%20the%20Antarctic%2C%20and%20indeed%20anywhere%20on%20the%20planet%2C%20are%20the%20nematodes.%20This%20is%20a%20small%20worm-like%20animal%2C%20that%20lives%20in%20and%20on%20top%20of%20the%20soil.%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F17712562%2F%5C%22%3ESome%20species%20like%20%3Cem%3EPanagrolaimus%20davidi%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0can%20tolerate%20their%20body%20cells%20freezing.%20They%20can%20also%20undergo%20a%20dormant%20state%20called%20diapause%20by%20dehydrating%20themselves%20(cryptobiosis)%2C%20which%20prevents%20ice%20crystals%20forming%20in%20their%20cells.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20group%20that%20uses%20this%20method%20for%20dealing%20with%20the%20cold%20Antarctic%20climate%20are%20the%20tardigrades%20(also%20known%20as%20water%20bears).%20Freezing%20can%20extend%20the%20life%20of%20this%20animal.%20In%20fact%2C%20one%20tardigrade%20species%20known%20as%C2%A0%3Cem%3EAcutuncus%20antarcticus%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fpii%2FS0011224015300134%3Fpes%3Dvor%26utm_source%3Dwiley%26getft_integrator%3Dwiley%5C%22%3Ewas%20frozen%20at%20-20%C2%B0C%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20defrosted%2030%20years%20later%20with%20no%20ill%20effects.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInvertebrates%2C%20make%20up%20an%20enormous%20proportion%20of%20all%20life%20on%20earth.%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nationalgeographic.com%2Fanimals%2Finvertebrates%23%3A%257E%3Atext%3DThis%2520is%2520by%2520far%2520the%2Cmillions%2520more%2520to%2520be%2520discovered.%5C%22%3EThere%20are%20so%20many%20species%20yet%20to%20be%20discovered%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20could%20help%20us%20unlock%20more%20secrets%20to%20survival%20in%20the%20most%20extreme%20environments%20and%20how%20this%20can%20benefit%20humans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFreeze%20tolerance%20and%20avoidance%20strategies%2C%20can%20enhance%20our%20knowledge%20of%20cryopreservation%20for%20medicine%20and%20organ%20transplants%2C%20improve%20food%20storage%2C%20aid%20climate%20adaptation%20and%20drive%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1002%2Fsmll.202201597%5C%22%3Einnovation%20in%20biotechnology%20and%20materials%20science%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Studying%20how%20these%20microscopic%20life%20forms%20endure%20extreme%20conditions%20could%20reveal%20secrets%20about%20the%20evolution%20of%20life%20on%20Earth%20and%20even%20offer%20insights%20into%20the%20future%20of%20cryopreservation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(%3Cstrong%3EAuthor%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Alex%20Dittrich%2C%C2%A0Senior%20Lecturer%20in%20Zoology%2C%20Nottingham%20Trent%20University)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%20Statement%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Alex%20Dittrich%20does%20not%20work%20for%2C%20consult%2C%20own%20shares%20in%20or%20receive%20funding%20from%20any%20company%20or%20organisation%20that%20would%20benefit%20from%20this%20article%2C%20and%20has%20disclosed%20no%20relevant%20affiliations%20beyond%20their%20academic%20appointment.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(This%20article%20is%20republished%20from%20T%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fglobal%5C%22%3Ehe%20Conversation%3C%2Fa%3E%20under%20a%20Creative%20Commons%20license.%20Read%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fhow-insects-and-the-smallest-animals-survive-antarctica-250314%5C%22%3Eoriginal%20article%3C%2Fa%3E.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(This%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20auto-generated%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1744536000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-04%2Ftgsd9118_antarctica_625x300_10_April_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fhow-insects-smallest-animals-survive-antarctica-8154076%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20Antarctica's%20freezing%20depths%2C%20tiny%20creatures%20have%20mastered%20survival%20tactics%20that%20could%20unlock%20secrets%20to%20extreme%20cold%20resistance%2C%20with%20implications%20for%20science%20and%20medicine.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22When%20Rani%20spoke%20about%20having%20a%20baby%20at%2037%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1744535721000%2C%22visual%22%3A%2